  "body": "I'm seeing over 900GB of disk writes after running geth for a few hours.  Network usage for the same time period is only 240MB. Where are all these writes coming from?\r\n\r\nI really don't want to wear out my SSD. \r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version:\r\n```\r\nGeth\r\nVersion: 1.7.3-stable\r\nArchitecture: amd64\r\nProtocol Versions: [63 62]\r\nNetwork Id: 1\r\nGo Version: go1.9.2\r\nOperating System: darwin\r\nGOPATH=\r\nGOROOT=/usr/local/Cellar/go/1.9.2/libexec\r\n```\r\nOS & Version: OSX 10.12.6\r\nCommit hash : N/A\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nLight amounts of data written to disk\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nOver 900 GB of disk writes after ~4 hours of running\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nRun macOS client in as system daemon\r\n[Plists for geth + ethminer config](https://gist.github.com/supercoffee/40ef81c8a5be72c647c299eeb9aac97f)\r\n\r\n#### Screenshot\r\n<img width=\"943\" alt=\"screen shot 2017-12-22 at 11 13 40 pm\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3880240/34317899-29ec81c4-e76e-11e7-848a-54689570ddbb.png\">\r\n\r\n<img width=\"943\" alt=\"screen shot 2017-12-22 at 11 18 53 pm\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3880240/34317911-ae09bec2-e76e-11e7-88bb-4692cef1d0be.png\">\r\n",
